---
description: Unit tests for pure logic; one behavior per test
alwaysApply: false
---

# Unit tests

- One unit (function / method / class) per file; **arrange / act / assert**.
- Pure: no real network, database, or shared filesystem (use temp dirs / in-memory).
- Mock at boundaries you don't own; never mock the unit under test.
- Cover happy path, **boundary**, and **error** cases; one behavior per test.
- Name: `<unit> <does X> when <condition>` (or framework equivalent).
- Deterministic—no time, randomness, or order dependence. Fast: seconds, not minutes.
